og.description: The District 47 seat was a highly contested race in the primaries, with four candidates vying for two seats. At the end of the primaries the final count established Steve Erdman and Karl Elmshaeuser as the winners. Erdman received 36 percent of the vote (2,945) and Elmshaeuser received 25 percent of the vote (2,053). They will advance to the general election in November.
og.title: Erdman, Elmshaeuser advance in District 47
